<subSubSection id="C34B6565FFFEFFF8FF284C0A2A9EFE13" pageId="4" pageNumber="559" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEE36EEFFFEFFF8FF284C0A2A9EFE13" blockId="4.[151,1437,289,460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis id="B925EAFCFFFEFFF8FF284C0A2B65FEE4" bold="true" box="[151,274,289,315]" pageId="4" pageNumber="559">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C514D6DFFFEFFF8FEA54C082BC3FEE3" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1881" box="[282,436,290,316]" class="Arachnida" family="Hahniidae" genus="Iberina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mazarredoi">
<emphasis id="B925EAFCFFFEFFF8FEA54C082BC3FEE3" box="[282,436,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="559">I. mazarredoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D6DFFFEFFF8FCA74C0929F9FEE3" box="[792,910,290,316]" class="Arachnida" family="Hahniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hahniinae">Hahniinae</taxonomicName>
, with spinnerets arranged in a transverse row. Representatives of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D6DFFFEFFF8FE5B4C6D2841FEBF" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1881" box="[484,566,326,352]" class="Arachnida" family="Hahniidae" genus="Iberina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B925EAFCFFFEFFF8FE5B4C6D2841FEBF" box="[484,566,326,352]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="559">Iberina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other genera of the subfamily by the combination of the following characteristics: the clypeus protrudes in profile, and is usually higher than the two ALE; presence of a strong, spur-like patellar apophysis; and a curved tibial apophysis that is serrated at its end and has a discoidal bulbus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
